5: All right, I've made up my mind!
11:
No, but really. It wouldn't be much
fun to go alone, right? No reason for
me to waste my time.
15:
From what I've heard, maybe I would
have found a little more success if I
brought Gerard along...
19: Ugh, stop following us! Let GO!
28:
Hey, it's you, Sho! You came at just
the right time. Help me do
something about these guys here!
34: Ah, h-hey! I told you to stop pulling!
47:
Nimbus? What the hell is
happening?!
50:
Damn it!
Tch, go ahead and run, Fluke! We'll
find you!
56:
We're on vacation, right? Why are
we involving ourselves in trouble like
this?
63:
His name is Fluke. For a number of
different reasons, he's being hunted
down by this town's mafia.
68:
He was involved with the big
cheese's girl. Some sort of affair,
apparently.
75:
N-no, that's not true! We were lovers.
She was mine first!
82:
Well... Even after he got dumped, he
kept following her around and got
into trouble...
90:
So we're on the bad guy's side this
time? Why should we be helping
him?
95:
Well... Nina... Uh, someone I know
asked for help.
98:
This guy doesn't have a place on the
island anymore. We'll have a ship at
harbor before dawn, so we've just
gotta lay low until then.
102: Why do I gotta help out with this?!
106:
I need help getting the boat ready.
Besides, I've got nothing to worry
about if you're around, right?
109:
I-I didn't do anything wrong! She
was taken away from me!
118:
Hmm... Oh? Have you been awake
this whole time, Sho?
122:
I was listening to that man whine on
and on, but then I remembered a lot
of things and I couldn't get to sleep.
125:
Even if I had to force it, I should have
invited Ayumu to come along...
130:
I guess Alk was still a little
shell-shocked from earlier.
135:
No, it's just... he said he was going to
go fishing. Alone. He said it so
emotionlessly I kinda laughed.
140:
Ahaha. Well... He's still a kid like us,
after all.
145:
Yeah, but him especially! Even just
having a slightly raunchy
conversation makes him get all sad.
147:
He's older and bigger than we are,
and he's even got some nasty scar
now... But on the inside? The guy
hasn't changed a bit.
152:
Maybe he just acts a certain way
around you?
155:
He doesn't seem to be too aware of
it, but he's super famous in
Palpebra. Nobody knows the limits
of what he can do!
160:
...Well, it's not like I don't get it. 
I couldn't help but wonder, 
"Why'd this guy give up on being 
human?"
165:
But you're great too, Sho. They call
you the Flying Prince, don't you? I'd
say that's pretty impressive!
175:
Evan, Yuna, that Walter guy... You're
all much more impressive than I am.
178:
I'm just some dude who got his
powers for free like a cheater.
182:
You're gonna put yourself down like
that? Even with all the part-time
work you do?
187:
Well, even I can't shirk basic
responsibilities.
192:
Hey, Sho. Sometimes I wonder if I've
been holding everyone else back.
196:
Huh? Sounds like you're overthinking
something?
201:
Maybe... So I'll try to avoid doing
that! After all, there aren't too many
people who can say they've herded
sheep with Alk before!
207:
I was young once too, you know... 
My girlfriend and I, we...
211:
I wish you'd stop finding excuses to
bring up your past...
216:
Ohh, Ohhhh! Ah, AH! HIYAH! No,
please, STOP!
219:
Hey Nimbus. We're out on open
water, and they don't know what we
look like yet, either. Can I do the
thing?
228: Heh-heh! Time to go all out!
245:
No way they'll catch up to us like
this! Right, Fluke?
249:
Y-yes, I do! Th-they're coming to get
me!
252:
Right, cool! In that case, things'll turn
out just fine for you!
263:
Ahaha. Sho's quite impressive, isn't
he?
267:
I'm glad you're done with that other
business that came up. I'm sure Sho
will be happy to see you.
272:
Yes. We made a promise to go pick
up ladies together.
276:
Ah... That's... You should, uh... Not
follow through with that...
280: Do you think so? Oh, that's too bad...
